
Most of the variables have filenames of the form object_fit2out*, indicating a single file combining the data from both channels and including a simultaneous fit to both. I think the final number in these filenames is the number of Fourier terms in the astrophysical model. The columns in these files are: (1)time in hours, (2)normalized raw flux, (3)full model of systematic and astrophysical variations, (4)residuals from full model, (5)normalized corrected flux, (6)model of astrophysical variations, ch1 only, (7)model of astrophysical variations, ch2 only. Note that columns 6 and 7 are intended to be plotted as model-fits to the data in column 5. Since these files combine ch1 (3.6 microns) and ch2 (4.5 microns), we expect column 6 to fit only the ch1 data well and column 7 to fit the ch2 data.

To determine which lines correspond to channel 1 and channel 2, use the following key:

2M0036_fit2out06.txt
channel1: lines 1-215
channel2: lines 216-375
2M0050_fit2out01.txt
channel1: lines 1-358
channel2: lines 359-544
