For two objects, no self-consistent dual-channel fit was possible, so the channels are fit independently. In these cases there is a separate file for each channel. The columns in these files are as follows: (1)time in hours, (2)normalized raw flux, (3)full model of systematic and astrophysical variations, (4)normalized corrected flux, (5)model of astrophysical variations, (6)residuals from full model. Note that, again, column 5 is intended to be plotted as a model-fit to the data in column 4. Here are the filenames:

SDSS1043_fitout06c.txt (ch1)
SDSS1043_fitout02b.txt (ch2)
2M1507_fitout08.txt (ch1)
2M1507_fitout02_ch2.txt (ch2)
